Package org.cytoscape.dyn.internal.view.layout.algorithms.standard

Interface Summary
Distance<T> Distance is an interface for classes which calculate the distance between one node and another.
Layout<T> Layout is a generalized interface for returning (x,y) coordinates from nodes.
ShortestPath<T> ShortestPath is an interface for algorithms that calculate shortest paths.
 

Class Summary
AbstractLayout<T> AbstractLayout is an abstract class for implementations of Layout.
BFSDistanceLabeler<T> BFSDistanceLabeler labels each node in the graph according to the BFS distance from the start node(s).
DistanceStatistics DistanceStatistics computes the statistics relating to vertex-vertex distances in a graph.
KKLayout<T> KKLayout implements the Kamada-Kawai algorithm for node layout.
UnweightedShortestPath<T> UnweightedShortestPath computes the shortest path distances for graphs whose edges are not weighted (using BFS).
